WEBVTT

NOTE English narration for the current Synthesis product overview

1.1
00:00:00.324 --> 00:00:04.800
Welcome to Synthesis, a traceable workspace for systematic reviews and meta-analyses.

1.2
00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:10.101
This overview follows a review from its protocol through screening, synthesis, and reporting.

1.3
00:00:10.335 --> 00:00:16.956
What you see is the seeded demonstration project, using the same workflows your team will use.

2.1
00:00:17.393 --> 00:00:21.783
Start by creating a project and assigning team roles.

2.2
00:00:22.121 --> 00:00:32.543
In Protocol, record the review question, narrative and structured PICO, eligibility criteria, outcomes, search plan, exclusion reasons, and analysis plan.

2.3
00:00:32.809 --> 00:00:34.787
Publish a version before screening.

2.4
00:00:34.958 --> 00:00:39.679
Later edits require an amendment note, so the methods history remains visible.

3.1
00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:48.634
Add each database as a source, then upload RIS, BibTeX, CSV, or NBIB exports.

3.2
00:00:49.211 --> 00:00:54.117
Synthesis previews every record and preserves parse errors before you commit a batch.

3.3
00:00:54.703 --> 00:00:58.046
The project always knows where each citation came from.

4.1
00:00:59.218 --> 00:01:01.969
Run duplicate detection before screening.

4.2
00:01:02.466 --> 00:01:08.635
Exact DOI and PMID matches sit alongside title-based suggestions for human review.

4.3
00:01:09.253 --> 00:01:15.045
Merge a pair, reject it, or undo a merge later; the original provenance is retained.

5.1
00:01:15.856 --> 00:01:20.485
Assign title-and-abstract and full-text work to one or more reviewers.

5.2
00:01:21.016 --> 00:01:30.145
The queue is keyboard first: I includes, E excludes, M marks maybe, N opens a note, and J skips.

5.3
00:01:30.587 --> 00:01:34.458
When blinding is enabled, reviewers cannot see one another's decisions.

5.4
00:01:34.986 --> 00:01:40.325
Disagreements become conflicts for an adjudicator, while agreed decisions advance automatically.

6.1
00:01:40.932 --> 00:01:46.977
The full-text workspace tracks retrieval attempts, attached PDFs, and screening status together.

6.2
00:01:47.647 --> 00:01:50.140
Included reports advance to studies.

6.3
00:01:50.816 --> 00:01:57.758
A full-text exclusion must use a configured reason, keeping PRISMA counts and exclusion tables consistent.

7.1
00:01:58.680 --> 00:02:03.903
Build a typed, versioned extraction template, publish it, and assign extractors.

7.2
00:02:04.455 --> 00:02:12.453
The living table resolves values in a clear order: adjudicated first, then consensus, then a single completed value.

7.3
00:02:13.460 --> 00:02:19.905
Evidence anchors reopen the exact supporting page and quote, and CSV export is always close at hand.

8.1
00:02:20.537 --> 00:02:24.577
For risk of bias, clone a standard instrument or build your own.

8.2
00:02:25.174 --> 00:02:33.468
Synthesis includes RoB 2, ROBINS-I, QUADAS-2, Newcastle-Ottawa, JBI, and AMSTAR 2.

8.3
00:02:34.252 --> 00:02:41.852
Reviewers assess domains independently; the traffic-light summary shows agreement, disagreements, and adjudicated judgments.

9.1
00:02:42.525 --> 00:02:49.708
Map extraction fields to an outcome once, and pooled results refresh as finalized evidence changes.

9.2
00:02:50.645 --> 00:03:04.714
Fixed and random effects, forest plots, prediction intervals, funnel plots, and small-study diagnostics are generated from deterministic statistical code, with incomplete or excluded studies called out.

10.1
00:03:05.248 --> 00:03:12.292
On the GRADE tab, Synthesis drafts five certainty domains from the pooled evidence and risk-of-bias results.

10.2
00:03:12.976 --> 00:03:16.271
Every judgment and rationale stays human-editable.

10.3
00:03:16.975 --> 00:03:22.505
Mark an assessment reviewed only when the evidence is current; source changes flag it as stale.

11.1
00:03:23.025 --> 00:03:30.943
AI assistance in Synthesis is optional, and it is designed as a second set of eyes—not an automated decision-maker.

11.2
00:03:32.124 --> 00:03:40.622
During title-and-abstract screening, it can score and prioritize citations, then show reviewers a suggested decision and rationale.

11.3
00:03:41.851 --> 00:03:51.369
For extraction and risk of bias, it can read the linked PDF, propose values or domain judgments, and surface supporting quotes with page references.

11.4
00:03:52.671 --> 00:03:58.627
In GRADE, it can draft per-domain rationale from the current pooled results and protocol context.

11.5
00:03:59.980 --> 00:04:02.767
Suggestions stay separate from the authoritative record.

11.6
00:04:03.318 --> 00:04:10.275
A reviewer chooses what to apply, existing work is protected, and accepted changes follow the normal audit trail.

12.1
00:04:11.260 --> 00:04:19.927
The Summary of Findings brings together study counts, participants, relative effects, anticipated absolute effects, and certainty.

12.2
00:04:20.564 --> 00:04:24.026
Download the table as CSV when it is ready for your report.

13.1
00:04:25.976 --> 00:04:30.413
PRISMA counts are computed live from the same decisions that drive the workflow.

13.2
00:04:30.850 --> 00:04:37.933
Save a frozen snapshot for a submission, and download the publication-ready flow diagram as SVG or PNG.

14.1
00:04:38.552 --> 00:04:43.389
Finally, the audit trail records who changed what, when, and why.

14.2
00:04:44.072 --> 00:04:46.753
Role-aware filtering preserves reviewer blinding.

14.3
00:04:47.526 --> 00:04:54.784
Together with capability-gated exports, it gives the review a defensible chain from source record to final conclusion.

15.1
00:04:55.347 --> 00:04:58.499
Synthesis now keeps review coordination beside the evidence.

15.2
00:04:58.499 --> 00:05:07.955
Use project channels and direct messages for questions, mentions to bring in the right colleague, and assignment messages with due dates and per-person completion.

15.3
00:05:07.955 --> 00:05:12.683
Unread badges show where attention is needed without exposing another project's activity.

16.1
00:05:13.413 --> 00:05:19.071
The notification bell brings direct messages, manuscript mentions, and assigned work into one inbox.

16.2
00:05:19.071 --> 00:05:27.960
Each item links back to its project context, and read state stays synchronized as the team moves between conversations and evidence tasks.

17.1
00:05:28.713 --> 00:05:33.463
Configure institutional proxy and OpenURL links once at the organization level.

17.2
00:05:33.463 --> 00:05:38.212
Each full-text record then offers DOI, PubMed, and library resolver routes.

17.3
00:05:38.212 --> 00:05:49.007
Owners can also run legal open-access retrieval through Unpaywall and Europe PMC, with successful files following the same validation and attempt history as manual uploads.

18.1
00:05:49.747 --> 00:05:55.329
The reference library brings included studies, methods papers, and background sources together.

18.2
00:05:55.329 --> 00:06:01.841
Add by DOI or PMID, paste RIS or BibTeX, or enter a record manually.

18.3
00:06:01.841 --> 00:06:07.424
Format Vancouver, AMA, APA, or NLM bibliographies and export to reference managers.

18.4
00:06:07.424 --> 00:06:10.215
A guideline family shares one library.

19.1
00:06:10.947 --> 00:06:18.741
Draft the manuscript section by section with assignments, editing locks, autosave, comments, mentions, version history, and approval states.

19.2
00:06:18.741 --> 00:06:25.669
Insert citations from the project library; the reference list follows first-use order and the selected style.

19.3
00:06:25.669 --> 00:06:30.432
Export the current manuscript as DOCX when the team is ready.

20.1
00:06:31.180 --> 00:06:37.815
For multi-question guidelines, create a guideline hub and add one full review for each PICO question.

20.2
00:06:37.815 --> 00:06:43.620
Teams can also convert an existing standalone review without recreating its evidence or history.

20.3
00:06:43.620 --> 00:06:51.498
The hub holds shared context, chat, references, and general manuscript sections, while each PICO keeps its complete review workflow.

21.1
00:06:52.247 --> 00:06:59.774
The compiled preview assembles the guideline's general sections followed by each PICO question, with one bibliography across the family.

21.2
00:06:59.774 --> 00:07:08.489
Full DOCX export is enabled only when the caller can read every included sub-project, so a partial guideline is never produced silently.

22.1
00:07:09.213 --> 00:07:20.346
That is the current Synthesis workspace: one connected system for evidence review, team coordination, reference management, manuscript development, and multi-question guidelines.

22.2
00:07:20.346 --> 00:07:26.707
Open the user guide for task-by-task instructions, role guidance, shortcuts, and troubleshooting.
